Detailed Description

This class administrates direct routing (non-via) questions.

Each such question is divided into request packets for a single map. The packet is sent to the RouteModule, and the reply packets are handled and administrated to create new request packets until the route is completed.

Member Enumeration Documentation

enum RouteSender::state_t [private]
 

The possible states of this object.

Enumeration values:
START_ROUTING  The state that is entered at the start.

Routing on this level until we either reach dest or hit the roof for this level routing.

TRANSIT_FINDING  Before we send a request to m_higherLevelRouteSender, we need to find out what maps to look for destinations in and what nodes to use as destinations on the higher level.
HIGHER_ROUTING  Routing on higher level by using m_higherLevelRouteSender.

While in this state, all packets are just passed on to or from the child m_higherLevelRouteSender.

CUTOFF_END_ROUTING  Routing from higher level to lower level in order to get a cutoff or a real route.
CUTOFF_HIGHER_ROUTING  More routing on higher level.

Hopefully CUTOFF_END_ROUTING will make all routes on higher level disappear.

END_ROUTING  Routing from higher level destinations down to detail destination on this level.
DONE  We have finished the routing.

Either finished routing or something is wrong.

set< uint32 > *  lowerLevelDestMaps = NULL,
RouteAllowedMap *  allowedMaps = NULL
) 
 

Standard constructor, taking origins and destinations to create a question.

Furthermore, if the route is a via route, and this part of the route is not the last, 'allDestInfoList' is a list that contains the destinations in the total question from user. Finally 'pref' is the object containing information about the user preferences.

Parameters:
user The request user which will be used for user rights.
request Request to get packetID:s from.
origInfoList A list of the origins.
destInfoList List of all destinations.
allDestInfoList List of all final destinations. If NULL destInfoList is used instead and only one route to the cheapest destination is calculated if not nbrBestDests is set.
pref The driver preferences.
routingInfo RoutingInfo about the map levels etc.
disturbances The disturbances that should be added to the SubRoutePackets.
nbrBestDests The number of destinations to calculate routes to. If MAX_UINT32 allDestInfoList will decide.
level The current routing level. Should only be used internally or be 0.
externalCutOff Used internally to avoid too much routing on higher level.
calcCostSums Internally used. Will be true if nbrBestDests != MAX_UINT32. Means that the sum of cost a-c should be calculated and returned by the RM. (for distsort).
dontSendSubRoutes Means that the nodes in the subroutes should not be sent to save network bandwith. Used internally. Will be true if nbrBestDests == MAX_UINT32. (For distsort).
lowerLevelDestMaps Destination maps on low level.
allowedMaps The allowed maps to route on, NULL means all.

int RouteSender::calcNbrDests (  const OrigDestInfoList *  allDestInfoList,
const OrigDestInfoList *  destInfoList,
uint32  nbrBestDests
)  [static, private]
 

Returns the number of routes to return in the answer.

If allDestInfoList is NULL and nbrBestDests is MAX_UINT32 one route will be calculated. If allDestInfoList is != NULL routes to all destinations will be calculated (for via-routes). If nbrBestDests is set, that number decides how many routes should be calced.

bool RouteSender::createAndEnqueueSubRouteRequest (   )  [private]
 

Takes new SubRoutes from m_requestSubRouteContainer and creates an outgoing packet container from them.

This is then enqueued in m_outgoingQueue, waiting for the next getNextPacket. Unless Traffic info is needed, then the packet is created and sent later.

Returns:
true if a packet is created.

uint32 RouteSender::getCutOff (   )  const [private]
 

Returns the current cutoff.

This is used for an experiment where we try to find the real cutoff when routing on higher level by going to low level and route to the dest and then continue on higher level where there will probably be no more routes to route on.

ServerSubRouteVectorVector* RouteSender::getRoute (   ) 
 

Goes through the m_finishedServerSubRouteVector and backtracks the finished routes.

Each of these is a ServerSubRouteVector. The ServerSubRouteVectorVector returned should be deleted by the caller when finished. Use getStatus() to find out if the routing was succesful.

Returns:
A ServerSubRouteVectorVector containing all the ServerSubRouteVectors that represent finished routes to the requested destinations.

ServerSubRouteVectorVector* RouteSender::getSortedRoute (   ) 
 

Calls getRoute and sorts the routes, cheapest first.

Returns:
A sorted ServerSubRouteVectorVector containing all the ServerSubRouteVectors that represent finished routes to the requested destinations.
